One after another his plans miscarried, friends failed, and enemies triumphed; and when Augustus, Antony, and Lepidus, who controlled the troops, united to form the second triumvirate, with the avowed object of the partition of the powers of the state among themselves, nothing was left for him but to flee before the proscription in which his name was foremost.
